            , and 
               <persName id="t18270913-227-defend1961" type="defendantName">
                  JAMES 
                  PAGET
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-defend1961" type="surname" value="PAGET"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-defend1961" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-defend1961" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , were indicted for <rs id="t18270913-227-off1283" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-off1283" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-off1283" type="offenceSubcategory" value="animalTheft"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18270913-227-cd1284" type="crimeDate">12th of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-227-off1283 t18270913-227-cd1284"></join>, at St. Leonard, Bromley, 1 gelding, price 21l.
            </rs>, the property of 
               <persName id="t18270913-227-victim1962" type="victimName">
                  Joseph 
                  Kain
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-victim1962" type="surname" value="Kain"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-victim1962" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-victim1962" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-227-off1283 t18270913-227-victim1962"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>MR. JOSEPH KAIN. I am a <rs id="t18270913-227-viclabel1285" type="occupation">shipowner</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-227-victim1962 t18270913-227-viclabel1285"></join>, and live at <placeName id="t18270913-227-crimeloc1286">St. Leonard's, Bromley, in Middlesex</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-227-crimeloc1286" type="placeName" value="St. Leonard's, Bromley, in Middlesex"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-227-crimeloc1286" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-227-off1283 t18270913-227-crimeloc1286"></join>. On the morning of Tuesday, the 12th of July, I lost a gelding out of a field, at the back of my house - I had seen it secure about ten o'clock the night before; the gate was then locked. On Tuesday morning my gardener came and told me the gate was broken open, and the gelding gone - I had handbills printed, and advertised it in the Times Newspaper - and on the Sunday evening, three Bow-street patrols came to me - I know the gelding to be mine; I know nothing of the prisoners.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-227-person1963">
                  FREDERICK 
                  GROSSMITH
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1963" type="surname" value="GROSSMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1963" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1963" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Bow-street officer. About half-past two o'clock in the morning of the 12th of July, I was with McWilliams and Tyrrell, in Church-row, Bethnal-green; it was just then getting light. I saw Hawkins riding on a gelding, at the corner of Busby-street, which leads out of Church-row - I suspected all was not right, and ran after him; he was only walking - I pursued him up Busby-street, and when I came up with him, I asked him whose horse that was; he hesitated a minute or two, and then said, he was a drover, and was coming from Romford, that about a quarter of a mile below Bow-bridge, a man in a fustian coat hired him to ride the horse to Church-street, Bethnal-green, and he was to have 1s. - but he was then riding away from Church-street - Tyrrell had got up by this time; he took Hawkins; I lead the horse to the corner of Brick-lane; McWilliams went to the farther end of Church-street, near Shoreditch, where Hawkins said the man was to wait for him - he returned in about ten minutes, and said there was no one waiting; that nobody was there but the watchman - we then took Hawkins to Bethnal-green watch-house. Tyrrell and I took the horse away, and at the corner of Hare-street, Brick-lane, we saw Hitchcock coming along - this was about six hundred yards from where we met Hawkins; we took him, and Tyrrell found a quantity of oats in his pocket; he was walking toward Church-street - we took him to the watch-house - we asked him where he had been - he said in the brick fields all night; we said nothing to him before we searched him. We asked Hawkins, in his presence, if he was the man who gave him the horse; he said No; we locked them up. I shewed the same horse to Mr. Kain, who claimed it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-227-person1964">
                  ROBERT 
                  TYRRELL
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1964" type="surname" value="TYRRELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1964" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1964" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. On the 12th of July I saw Hawkins go down Busby-street, with the horse, as my brother officer has stated; we saw Hitchcock; he was dressed as Hawkins had described - I stopped him and found some oats in his pocket. I then took off his hat, and found in the lining of it, the remains of some oats - I asked Hawkins if he was the man; he said No.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-227-person1965">
                  JOHN 
                  McWILLIAMS
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1965" type="surname" value="McWILLIAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1965" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1965" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was with the other officers - I left them at the top of Brick-lane, and went to the end of Church-street, where Hawkins said he was to meet the man. I waited there ten minutes or more, and could see no man; I enquired of the watchman; then came back and told them nobody had been seen there.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-227-person1966">
                  JOSEPH 
                  ADAMS
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1966" type="surname" value="ADAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1966" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1966" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a street-keeper. I received information from Worship-street, that Paget' was wanted - I met him on the 28th of July, took him, and told him I wanted him for horse-stealing; he said, rather than go to the watch-house, he would go to Garton, as he knew it was all right - we went part of the way and he ran off, down an entry; I called out, and he was stopped at the end of Longalley - I took him to Garton, who said he was the person wanted.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-227-person1967">
                  WILLIAM 
                  WILLIAMS
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1967" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1967" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1967" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. At a quarter to ten o'clock on the 28th of July, I heard Adams calling Stop him! I stopped Paget in Meeting-house-court, Longalley; he said "Let me go, it is the street-keeper after me."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-227-person1968">
                  JOSHUA 
                  ARMSTRONG
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1968" type="surname" value="ARMSTRONG"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1968" type="given" value="JOSHUA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1968" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. After Hawkins was taken, I went to Paget's house but could not find him at home.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-227-person1969">
                  THOMAS 
                  GARTON
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1969" type="surname" value="GARTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1969" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1969" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Armstrong; in consequence of Hawkins' confession before the Magistrate, I went to take Paget.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-227-person1970">
                  THOMAS 
                  WATERS
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1970" type="surname" value="WATERS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1970" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1970" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer of Worship-street. I went into the lock-up room, and Hawkins said it was very hard he should suffer as an innocent man, and wanted to tell me something - I said, "Don't say any thing to me; if you have anything to say, I will take you in to the Magistrate;" what he said was taken down - I made him no promise or threat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-227-person1971">
                  RICHARD 
                  SKILLERN
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1971" type="surname" value="SKILLERN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1971" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1971" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable of Bow-street. Hitchcock was apprehended on the 12th, and discharged; after that I heard he was wanted - I went and took him again on the 13th.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-227-person1972">
                  WILLIAM 
                  KAIN
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1972" type="surname" value="KAIN"></interp>
