                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1972" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Grossmith shewed me the horse; it was mine - it is worth twenty guineas.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-227-person1973">
                  JOSHUA 
                  ARMSTRONG
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1973" type="surname" value="ARMSTRONG"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1973" type="given" value="JOSHUA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1973" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . (Looking at the examinations returned by the Magistrate.) This is signed by Mr. Twyford; and I saw Hawkins make his mark to it (read.)</p>
               <p>"John Hitchcock came to me yesterday, at one o'clock, and told me Mr. Paget wanted to speak to me about a horse, it was a job to fetch a horse. I went, and Hitchcock and Roberts were there; they asked if I would go to fetch the horse - we went to the bridge at Mile-end, and Hitchcock told me to wait there while he went into a lane; when he returned, he led a chesnut-coloured horse, and told me to ride on to Church-street, Bethnal-green, and when I got to Church-street I was stopped - Hitchcock told me it was a Justice of the Peace's horse. 
               <persName id="t18270913-227-person1974">
                  CHARLES 
                  HAWKINS
               <interp inst="t18270913-227-person1974" type="surname" value="HAWKINS"></interp>
